Territory2AlignmentLog.name: Territory2AlignmentLog
Territory2AlignmentLog.description: Represents the start and end status of a territory assignment rule run job.

EndTime.description: The date and time when the assignment rule run job finished.

Filter.description: Criteria to filter the rule jobs. For example, {RULE_LAST_MOD_DATE_FORM=2021-08-31, RULE_LAST_MOD_DATE_TO=2021-09-15}.

RunAsId.description: ID of the Salesforce user who started the assignment rule run job.

StartTime.description: The date and time when the user started the assignment rule run job.

Status.description: The status of the assignment rule run job.

Territory2Id.description: The ID of the territory for which the assignment rule run was performed. If the assignment rule run was for the territory model, this value is null.

Territory2ModelId.description: The ID of the territory model for which the assignment rule run was performed.

Territory2AlignmentLog.accessRules: Available if Sales Territories has been enabled.
